    • Method Detail

      • getSolver

        public static AbstractSolutionNode getSolver(Formula goal,
                             RuleSet rules,
                             Substitution parentSolution)
        This method generates a new child goal node appropriate for the parameter goal Formula:
        • If the Formula is a Predicate, this method returns a PredicateSolutionNode.
        • If the Formula is an AndOperator, this method returns an AndSolutionNode.
        Parameters:
        goal - The Formula for which a solution node is desired, not null.
        rules - The RuleSet that defines the logical basis used for resolution, not null.
        parentSolution - The Substitution solution that exists prior to the creation of this node, not null.
        Returns:
        an AbstractSolutionNode appropriate for the type of the parameter goal Formula.
